race.comment: Decimated by the scratchings. RUINS OF ROME (1) is a talented type resuming from a long spell. Tackled stakes class over the carnival but comes back to the right level for the return and presents on the back of two trials. Will be winding up late. GORBACHEV (6) also resumed in that same race at the Gold Coast and was a narrow third. Has a low draw and will push forward. ABENDER (2) went to the paddock a maiden winner and has plenty of upside. Will give a start but charge late. NORTH POLE (8) is resuming from a lay-off. Fitter for a trial and has handled the going. Opened last campaign with a win at Ipswich over 1240m. Has lots of early pace and can give a sight.
